@startuml
'Application Design for smart Locker
participant Resident as P
participant WeResident as W
participant WeID as ID
participant WeService as S

=== Provider Login Into Provider App ===
P -> W: Send username:password /login
alt Provider already exist
W --> ID: Get Token by username:password\n/oauth/authorize
ID --> W: Return Token to WeResident
W -> P: Return {"token": "jwt-token"}
end
=== Provider Query/Search Service ===
P -> S: Query services including token\n /weservices/services\nHeader\n Authorization: Bear <b>{jwt-token}</b>
note right P: Query Service schema \n {"query":"string","status":12}
alt above token is valid
    S --> ID: verify token
    ID --> S: 200
    S -> P: Response services data
note right P: Service Data Array schema \n {[{"id":"string","company":"string","name":"string","rate":4.2,"image":"image.png"},{}],\n"total":10,"currentPage":1,"perPage":5}
else Token is expired/invalid
    S --> ID: verify token
    ID --> S: 400
    S -> P: Response 401 status
end

=== Create Order(Request) ===
P -> S: Create Service\nPOST: /weservices/service/{serviceID}/order
note right P: Order Request schema \n {"resident":"$userID",\n"service":"$serviceID",\n"pricingModel":{},\n"noteDetail":"string",\n"address":"string",\n"schedule":Time}
S --> ID: verify token
ID --> S: 200
S -> P: Response Service Data(JSON)
P -> S: Comment(chat) in Order\n POST: /weservices/order/{orderID}/comment
note right P: Comment Data \n {"content":"string"}
S --> ID: verify token
ID --> S: 200
S -> P: 200
@enduml
